==Old English==
===Etymology===
Germanic ''*sunnen'', from Indo-European ''*sh₂un-'', ''*seh₂u̯ōl''.

''Germanic cognates:'' Old Frisian [[sunne#Old Frisian|sunne]], Old Saxon [[sunna]] (Dutch [[zon]]), Old High German [[sunna]] (German [[Sonne]]), Old Norse [[sunna]], Gothic [[𐍃𐌿𐌽𐌽𐍉]].

''Indo-European cognates:'' Saskrit [[स्वर्]], Greek [[ἥλιος]], Latin [[sol]], Old Church Slavonic [[слъньце]] (Russian [[солнце]]), Latvian [[saule|saũle]], Welsh [[haul]], 

